   inviwo  [--reset-window-state] [--update-workspaces-in-path <path>]

           file>] [--]


Where: 

   --reset-window-state
     Reset the window state of the Qt user interface including dock
     widgets. Use to fix a broken toolbar.

   --update-workspaces-in-path <path>
     Update all workspaces in path to the latest version

   --update-regression-workspaces
     Update regression workspaces of all modules to the latest version
     (located in '<module>/tests/regression/*')

   --update-workspaces
     Update workspaces of all modules to the latest version (located in
     '<module>/data/workspaces/*')

   --save-previews <path>
     Save processor previews to the supplied path

   -g <file name>,  --screengrab <file name>
     Specify default name of each screen grab.

   -s <file name>,  --snapshot <file name>
     Specify base name of each snapshot, or "UPN" string for processor
     name.

   -d <file name>,  --data <file name>
     Try and open a data file

   --version
     Displays version information and exits.

   -h,  --help
     Displays usage information and exits.

   -c,  --logconsole
     Write log messages to console (cout)

   -m <module search path>,  --module-search-path <module search path> 
      (accepted multiple times)
     Specify additional module search paths

   -l <logfile>,  --logfile <logfile>
     Write log messages to file.

   -n,  --nosplash
     Pass this flag if you do not want to show a splash screen.

   -q,  --quit
     Pass this flag if you want to close inviwo after startup.

   -o <output path>,  --output <output path>
     Specify output path

   -w <workspace file>,  --workspace <workspace file>

USAGE: 

   inviwo  [--reset-window-state] [--update-workspaces-in-path <path>]
           [--update-regression-workspaces] [--update-workspaces]
           [--save-previews <path>] [-g <file name>] [-s <file name>] [-d
           <file name>] [--version] [-h] [-c] [-m <module search path>] ...
           [-l <logfile>] [-n] [-q] [-o <output path>] [-w <workspace
           file>] [--]


Where: 

   --reset-window-state
     Reset the window state of the Qt user interface including dock
     widgets. Use to fix a broken toolbar.

   --update-workspaces-in-path <path>
     Update all workspaces in path to the latest version

   --update-regression-workspaces
     Update regression workspaces of all modules to the latest version
     (located in '<module>/tests/regression/*')

   --update-workspaces
     Update workspaces of all modules to the latest version (located in
     '<module>/data/workspaces/*')

   --save-previews <path>
     Save processor previews to the supplied path

   -g <file name>,  --screengrab <file name>
     Specify default name of each screen grab.

   -s <file name>,  --snapshot <file name>
     Specify base name of each snapshot, or "UPN" string for processor
     name.

   -d <file name>,  --data <file name>
     Try and open a data file

   --version
     Displays version information and exits.

   -h,  --help
     Displays usage information and exits.

   -c,  --logconsole
     Write log messages to console (cout)

   -m <module search path>,  --module-search-path <module search path> 
      (accepted multiple times)
     Specify additional module search paths

   -l <logfile>,  --logfile <logfile>
     Write log messages to file.

   -n,  --nosplash
     Pass this flag if you do not want to show a splash screen.

   -q,  --quit
     Pass this flag if you want to close inviwo after startup.

   -o <output path>,  --output <output path>
     Specify output path

   -w <workspace file>,  --workspace <workspace file>
     Specify workspace to open

   --,  --ignore_rest
     Ignores the rest of the labeled arguments following this flag.


   Inviwo, Interactive Visualization Workshop, a rapid prototyping
